<H2>Upgrade All Dialog</H2>
<P>The Upgrade All Dialog allows you to confirm or cancel the upgrade of all installed
 packages for which there is an upgrade available.</P>
<P>It is shown from the iconbar menu, the main window menu and from a button on the
Update Lists windows which is enabled if upgrades are available.</P>
<P>It shows the following information
<UL>
<LI>Names of the packages that will be upgraded</LI>
<LI>List of packages that need to be removed. Usually because they have been replaced by this
package or one of its dependencies or conflicts with this package</LI>
<LI>Totals of the number of packages to be installed and removed</LI>
<LI>Total size of the downloads required to install these packages</LI>
</UL>
</P>
<P>
Press the Upgrade All button to install these packages and any dependencies
and remove any clashing packages.
This will then display the <A HREF="commit.htm">Commit Window</A> which
will show the progress of the upgrade and report if it is successful
or not.</P>
<P>
Press the Cancel button if you do not want to go ahead and upgrade these
packages.
</P>

